ommended notebook computer systems  The equipment recommended have been found through experience to be reliable and the manufacturers have consistently offered quality service  Information Technology has selected a DELL model which should meet everyones needs  This in no way implies that the systems are without fault or even that they are the best systems on the market at this time  You have the opportunity to customize your laptop according to your needs  Should you need further information or assistance in ordering a laptop  you may contact the Barracks Help Desk at  540  464 7888 or email Shawn Cain  The DELL laptop has a 4 year on site warranty and Apple MacBook Pro has an AppleCare Protection Plan which is recommended by IT  With the DELL onsite coverage  the laptop can be worked on at VMI  by our certified DELL technician  When purchasing a recommended model  a loaner laptop is available to users having equipment issues  You must first Click here  to review the Microsoft Campus Agreement before proceeding to the DELL or Apple website  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 